Secretary of State Antony Blinken, Secretary of Veterans Affairs Dennis McDonough, Deputy Homeland Security Advisor Josh Geltzer, Senior Response Official at Operation Allies Welcome Bob Fenton, and White House Director of Veterans Engagement in the Office of Public Engagement Saki Ververis held a virtual meeting with 75 veteran, military family, caregiver, and survivor organizations. The purpose of the meeting was to hear directly from these groups about their efforts to support veterans, military families, and Afghan allies in light of the recent withdrawal from Afghanistan. Secretary Blinken expressed his gratitude for their commitment and emphasized the importance of their voices and ongoing work. Secretary McDonough reaffirmed the Department of Veterans Affairs' commitment to collaborating with and supporting veterans organizations. Administration officials reiterated President Biden's commitment to allies and servicemembers and pledged to maintain engagement and partnership with these groups.